OL,6,FShah was charged with four offences
OL,7,Fincluded supplying vapes containing
OL,8,Fmore than the legal limit of 2
OL,9,Fmillilitres of nicotine-containing
OL,10,Fliquid, and supplying vapes without
OL,11,Fthe required health warnings and
OL,12,Finformation on the packaging.
OL,14,FIn court, Mr Shah pleaded guilty to
OL,15,Fall offences. He received a sentence
OL,16,Fof 32 weeks custody, suspended for 12
OL,17,Fmonths. In addition, the court imposed
OL,18,Fa #180 victim surcharge
